    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "15197672_19076b5e",
        "filename": "android/update-check/VersionExtractor.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 12,
      "author": {
        "id": 1079748
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-09-30T01:47:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is the jury out on std::string vs android::base::String?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 12,
        "startChar": 56,
        "endLine": 12,
        "endChar": 67
      },
      "revId": "33a460ce402d8e43d8cb1bf747b121bdb1e10a42",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "75439281_410b7432",
        "filename": "android/update-check/VersionExtractor.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 12,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-09-30T17:17:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "with C++11 addition there\u0027s no real reason to use String, as std::string is required to not have copy on write and to be contiguous in memory. AFAIK all existing implementations now have short string optimization",
      "parentUuid": "15197672_19076b5e",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 12,
        "startChar": 56,
        "endLine": 12,
        "endChar": 67
      },
      "revId": "33a460ce402d8e43d8cb1bf747b121bdb1e10a42",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "953c86f3_22de30fc",
        "filename": "android/update-check/VersionExtractor.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 12,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-09-30T17:17:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Well, requiring something to be const on an interface level adds some serious constraints to all implementation (e.g. caching, state preserving etc is banned). That\u0027s why I prefer not to have any const functions in interfaces unless I need them to be const (not just prefer const, but need it)",
      "parentUuid": "f86a1765_b93a4ba9",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 12,
        "startChar": 74,
        "endLine": 12,
        "endChar": 75
      },
      "revId": "33a460ce402d8e43d8cb1bf747b121bdb1e10a42",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
